    "scenario": "Three background indexer-pass completions land while the user is in mode_quiet_hours_user. Each completion mints an envelope with delivery_surface_class = not_delivered_held and a quiet_hours_user_policy suppression reason; durable chronology is preserved even though toast / os_notification / companion_push / lock_screen_summary are all suppressed. When the user's quiet-hours window exits, the three held envelopes release as one grouped digest (kind = mode_exit_grouped_digest, member_count = 3) grouped by source and severity — they do not replay as three independent toasts. The digest resolves through an activity_center_item linkback and a history_lane_row linkback so the user can still trace each indexer-pass run.",
